&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trust Doctor (ST1-2) post in Acute Medicine &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal United Hospital in Bath is looking to recruit a Trust Doctor (ST1-2) in Acute Medicine. This is a fixed term post until end of July 2021. Start date to be discussed with successful candidate, can be immediate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Medical Assessment Unit has 34 beds and is situated adjacent to the Emergency Department; the Acute Medicine team also look after an 18 bedded Short Stay ward, and a busy Medical Ambulatory Care area. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal United is a 565 bedded district general hospital, close to the center of the historic city of Bath, serving a catchment population of 500 000 people. Bath offers excellent shopping, entertainment and sports facilities. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates must have MBBS or an equivalent medical qualification at the time of application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal enquiries and arrangements to visit the department, please contact Dr Sarah Gillett, Acute Medicine Consultant through &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;sarahgillett@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
